---
import BaseLayout from "../layouts/BaseLayout.astro";
import BaseHead from "../layouts/BaseHead.astro";
import "../styles/index.css";

let json = [
  {
    title: "HIIT for creators",
    blurb:
      " An interface for fitness trainers doing HIIT classes over Zoom. Inspired during covid, made for my own trainer.",
    future: "",
    tech: [""],
  },
];
---

<html>
  <head>
    <BaseHead title="Home â€“ Dan Engel" />
    <link rel="stylesheet" href="../src/styles/index.css" slot="styles" />
    <style>
      #post-grid {
        display: grid;
        grid-template-columns: 1fr 0.3fr;
        width: 100%;
        height: 100%;
        position: relative;
        padding-inline-start: 1em;
        transition: 0.21s all;
        .titler {
          opacity: 1;
        }
        @media (width < 768px) {
          grid-template-columns: 1fr 0fr;
          .titler {
            opacity: 0;
            /* transform: scale(1.2, 1.2); */
            transform-origin: 150% -150%;
          }
        }
      }
      .exp-list {
        padding-block-end: 4em;
        background: var(--surface-1);
      }
      .exp-item__head {
        display: flex;
        justify-content: space-between;
        align-items: last baseline;
        margin-inline-end: 0px;
        border-block-end: 0.1rem solid var(--text-1);
        margin-block-end: 0.6rem;
      }
      .exp-item__links {
        display: flex;
        flex-direction: column;
        height: 100%;
        width: 4ch;
        text-align: center;

        align-self: center;
        a {
          padding-block: auto;
        }
      }
      .exp-item {
        width: 90%;
        border: 3px solid white;
        border-radius: 4px;
        margin-block-end: 1em;
        hr {
          margin-block: 0em;
          background-color: var(--text-1);
          /* padding: 0.01rem; */
          margin-block: 3px;
        }
      }
      .exp-item__content {
        padding-inline: 4px;
      }
      .titler {
        transition-property: opacity, transform;
        transition-duration: 0.2s, 0.5s;
        position: sticky;
        justify-self: flex-end;
        text-transform: uppercase;
        font-size: clamp(5em, 10vw + 4em, 22em);
        letter-spacing: -0.08cap;
        writing-mode: vertical-lr;
        margin-inline-start: 0em;
        padding-inline-end: 1em;
        overflow: hidden;
        height: fit-content;
        top: 0px;
        bottom: 0;
        margin: 0px -20%;
        z-index: 0;
        border-bottom-left-radius: 50em;
        @media (prefers-color-scheme: dark) {
          color: var(--text-1);
        }
        @media (prefers-color-scheme: light) {
          color: hsl(50, 90%, 60%);
        }
      }
      #circle {
        @media (prefers-color-scheme: dark) {
          mix-blend-mode: difference;
          background: linear-gradient(
            120deg,
            hsla(219, 43%, 71%, 1) 0.1%,
            hsla(0, 100%, 96%, 0.91) 47.9%,
            hsla(60, 94%, 60%) 180.2%
          );
        }
        @media (prefers-color-scheme: light) {
          mix-blend-mode: color-dodge;
          background: linear-gradient(
            600deg,
            rgb(0, 85, 231) 0.1%,
            hsla(297, 64%, 60%, 0.91) 47.9%,
            rgb(255, 255, 243) 180.2%
          );
        }
        height: 350px;
        width: 350px;
        aspect-ratio: 1/1;
        border-radius: 50%;
        position: absolute;
        left: 45%;
        bottom: 50%;
        z-index: 1;
        animation: rotate 42s infinite alternate ease-in-out;
      }
      @keyframes rotate {
        0% {
          transform: rotate(360deg) skewY(-20deg) translateY(70px);
        }
        20% {
          transform: translateX(100deg);
        }
        ,
        50% {
          transform: rotate(0deg) skewY(-50deg) skewX(-10deg);
        }
        100% {
          transform: rotate(-180deg) skewY(0deg) scale(4, 4);
        }
      }
    </style>
  </head>
  <body>
    <BaseLayout>
      <div slot="main-content" id="main-content">
        <div id="post-grid" slot="main-content">
          <div class="exp-list">
            <h1 style="padding-block-end: 0em">Little Experiments</h1>
            <p>often unpolished, usually done</p>
            <div class="exp-item">
              <div class="exp-item__head">
                <div>
                  <h2>Inky</h2>
                  <small>last commit: May 6, 2024</small>
                </div>
                <div class="exp-item__links" style="">
                  <a href="https://inky.dngl.cc/">try it</a>
                  <hr />
                  <a
                    style="margin-block-end:0em"
                    href="https://github.com/dengel29/hover-segmenter">code</a
                  >
                </div>
              </div>
              <div class="exp-item__content">
                <p>
                  <strong>Inspired by</strong> pop-up dictionary browser extensions
                  like Inkah
                </p>
                <p>
                  <strong>Tech</strong> is <a href="https://catalyst.rocks/"
                    >Catalyst</a
                  >, as much web tech as possible, catalyst, as much web tech as
                  possible
                </p>
                <p>
                  <strong>Wish List</strong>
                  <ul>
                    <li>
                      allow user to paste a link and get a <a
                        href="https://www.npmjs.com/package/@mozilla/readability"
                      >
                        "reader view"</a
                      > version of the article
                    </li>
                    <li></li>
                  </ul>
                </p>
              </div>
            </div>
            <div class="exp-item">
              <div class="exp-item__head">
                <div>
                  <h2>Tribe Has Spoken</h2>
                  <small>last commit: Apr 30, 2024</small>
                </div>

                <div class="exp-item__links" style="">
                  <a href="https://ths.dngl.cc/">try it</a>
                  <hr />
                  <a
                    style="margin-block-end:0em"
                    href="https://github.com/dengel29/tribe-has-spoken">code</a
                  >
                </div>
              </div>
              <div class="exp-item__content">
                <p>
                  <strong>A drag and drop</strong> interface for visualizing Survivor
                  votes
                </p>
                <p>
                  <strong>Inspired by</strong> a messy live-whiteboard session
                </p>
                <p>
                  <strong>Tech</strong> is <a href="https://catalyst.rocks/"
                    >Catalyst</a
                  >, as much web tech as possible, intersection observer and
                  mutation observer
                </p>
                <p>
                  <strong>Wish List</strong>
                  <ul>
                    <li>make it a little prettier</li>
                    <li>
                      generate workouts from selected focus (legs, arms, core,
                      etc.)
                    </li>
                    <li>provide a bank of workouts for inspiration</li>
                    <li>shuffle individual workouts with variations</li>
                  </ul>
                </p>
              </div>
            </div>
            <div class="exp-item">
              <div class="exp-item__head">
                <div>
                  <h2>HIIT For Creators</h2>
                  <small>last commit: Jul 2, 2021</small>
                </div>
                <div class="exp-item__links" style="">
                  <a href="https://hiit.dngl.cc/">try it</a>
                  <hr />
                  <a
                    style="margin-block-end:0em"
                    href="https://github.com/dengel29/exercise-stream/">code</a
                  >
                </div>
              </div>
              <div class="exp-item__content">
                <p>
                  <strong>Inspired by</strong> Zoom fitness classes during COVID,
                  livestream tools
                </p>
                <p>
                  <strong>Tech</strong> is just front-end Vue3. Transparent, draggable,
                  customizable elements for streaming.
                </p>
                <p>
                  <strong>Wish List</strong>
                  <ul>
                    <li>make it a little prettier</li>
                    <li>
                      generate workouts from selected focus (legs, arms, core,
                      etc.)
                    </li>
                    <li>provide a bank of workouts for inspiration</li>
                    <li>shuffle individual workouts with variations</li>
                  </ul>
                </p>
                <p>
                  <strong>I learned</strong>
                  <ul>
                    <li>
                      URL params for state is very cool and useful if you don't
                      care about the aesthetics of your URLs
                    </li>
                    <li>
                      i can't believe url aesthetics are a thing, but also my
                      website is as few letters as possible
                    </li>
                    <li>
                      vue's "computed" function is awesome. it's a good
                      framework tool in that it gives you a conceptional
                      organizational tool (I use it for calculating workout +
                      rest times)
                    </li>
                  </ul>
                </p>
              </div>
            </div>
            <div class="exp-item">
              <div class="exp-item__head">
                <div>
                  <h2>Lil Pathfinder</h2>
                  <small>last commit: Jul 5, 2021</small>
                </div>
                <div class="exp-item__links" style="">
                  <a href="https://maze.dngl.cc/">try it</a>
                  <hr />
                  <a
                    style="margin-block-end:0em"
                    href="https://github.com/dengel29/vue-pathfinder">code</a
                  >
                </div>
              </div>
              <div class="exp-item__content">
                <p>
                  <strong>Inspired by</strong> paths, mazes
                </p>
                <p>
                  <strong>Tech</strong> is just front-end Vue3. Also, Vuex a bit
                  of XState
                </p>
                <p>
                  <strong>Wish List</strong>
                  <ul>
                    <li>less griddy, more curvy</li>
                    <li>display as line between, rather than grid itself</li>
                  </ul>
                </p>
                <p>
                  <strong>I learned</strong>
                  <ul>
                    <li>
                      URL params for state is very cool and useful if you don't
                      care about the aesthetics of your URLs
                    </li>
                    <li>
                      i can't believe url aesthetics are a thing, but also my
                      website is as few letters as possible
                    </li>
                    <li>
                      vue's "computed" function is awesome. it's a good
                      framework tool in that it gives you a conceptional
                      organizational tool (I use it for calculating workout +
                      rest times)
                    </li>
                  </ul>
                </p>
              </div>
            </div>
          </div>
          <span class="titler">
            <span>lab</span>
            <div id="circle"></div>
          </span>
        </div>
      </div>
    </BaseLayout>
  </body>
</html>
